      <description>&lt;p&gt;Playing a &lt;strong&gt;rock show in a small club&lt;/strong&gt; as a drummer is about &lt;em&gt;power with control&lt;/em&gt;. You want the band to hit hard without overwhelming the room or wrecking the mix. Here’s a practical, gig-tested guide.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;tune-size-and-gear-choices-small-room--smart-choices&#34;&gt;Tune, Size, and Gear Choices (Small Room = Smart Choices)&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;  &lt;img&#xA;    src=&#34;https://www.anthonycastaneda.com/img/big-kit.jpg&#34;&#xA;    alt=&#34;C&amp;rsquo;mon, man&#34;&#xA;    loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;    &#xA;  /&gt;&#xA;  &lt;figcaption&gt;C&amp;rsquo;mon, man&lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Not everyone has access to more than one drum kit, but if you do, bring your smaller kit to the small club&lt;/p&gt;</description>
